transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I had ordered the, I think it was Viagra, Viagra AGV.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: As advertised. Well, that's not what I got.

Speaker 1: I got Suzenafil. It's the generic brand.

Speaker 2: Let me help you out, Wayne. Can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 1: Yeah, date of birth is 12-11-1957.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much. I see you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and you're right. They just, the pharmacy made an error and just sent you regular generic Viagra.

Speaker 2: Give me a second. I'm going to send you a replacement.

Speaker 1: Okay, I just put in a replacement order that they'll ship out to you tomorrow morning.

Speaker 2: So when you get this new bottle, on the bottle it's going to say AGV, but it's also going to say Greenstone.

Speaker 1: And Greenstone is the name of Pfizer's manufacturer in France.

Speaker 2: And then on the individual pills, the only number imprinted is going to be the number 100 for the milligrams.

Speaker 1: And those are the two ways you can confirm you received the Pfizer Viagra AGV.

Speaker 2: Because right now your bottle says APCO, and on your pills it has the letters AC followed by the numbers 390 or 3-something.

Speaker 1: Okay. I just know that's not what I ordered.

Speaker 2: Yeah, it's not.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so sometimes the pharmacy runs out of the AGV and they don't tell us, and they send generics, which causes issues.

Speaker 2: But I got you on there, correct?

Speaker 1: Are you sure? Because, yeah, this makes you look bad. It affects your integrity as far as I'm concerned anyway.

Speaker 2: Because with your advertising, which you sold me, two totally different things. So, okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no problem. I got you the correct stuff. You'll get it in about five days or less.

Speaker 2: Okay. Well, thank you very much. I appreciate that.

Speaker 1: No problem. Have a great day.

Speaker 2: Okay. All right. You too.

Speaker 1: Bye. Thanks. Bye.
